In a message dated 4/18/03 12:51:14 PM Central Daylight Time, 
airly2002@... writes:


> Blackstorm typed more buttons, hoping that that could help her to 
> heal more quickly.
> 

Whatever she did, it barely helped. Something was most definitely not right. 

Maxima's optics opened & flashed dimly. Her optics glanced at Blackstorm. She 
never knew her at Nightlight. But, then again, Maxima never knew her at all. 
Rather wary of another, she moved & shifted. She was weak & unable to 
confront what she may have believed Blackstorm to be a possible threat. She 
watched her for a moment, her optics glued to her like a hawk watching a 
mouse. Her long black claws flexed. 


--part1_199.18faa00e.2bd1e6d7_boundary
